text: North Shore is an electoral district of New South Wales. It was created in 1927, abolished in 1927 and recreated in 1981. It is a conservative electorate that has only ever been held by the Liberal Party as an electorate with one member, with the exception of two independents. North Shore is located on Sydney's North Shore, which is where it gets its name from. ==Election results== ==References== North shore
